ul.li:
Replace the ojdbc6.jar file in WLS_HOME\lib folder with one shipped with the application product, under the drivers directory of the SDEJ installation, e.g. D:\Curam\SDEJ\drivers;

where, the WLS_HOME variable points to the /server directory of the WebLogic Server installation, for example: d:\WLS\weblogic\server or /opt/wls/weblogic/server.
The copies of Oracle Thin drivers installed with WebLogic Server and other supporting files are installed in WLS_HOME\ext\jdbc\ directory. There is a subdirectory in this folder for each DBMS. If you need to revert to the version of the driver installed with WebLogic Server at any point, then you can copy the file from WLS_HOME\ext\jdbc\oracle\11g\ to WLS_HOME\lib folder.
